modules.description: Provides operations for defining and executing workflows that track changes in Git repositories, including fetching, building, testing, and deploying code. Works with Git commits, build artifacts, and deployment targets. Used to automate continuous integration tasks, ensuring that build statuses are updated in real-time as code changes.

Executes SSH commands on a remote host and tracks their output using a schedule and key. It operates on strings for hostnames and command arguments, and a schedule structure to manage execution timing. It ensures commands are only run when their parameters or cached results have changed.
